The course is for students who in their future work intend to teach history in forms 5 and 6. It gives an overview of the development of teaching history in Estonia and around the world, of the aims of teaching history and of other main problems related to the didactics of history. The main stress is laid on the contemporary theory and practice of teaching history. During the course students can apply their knowledge gained from the studies of educational sciences and didactics of other subjects. 4 hours of lectures, 32 hours of seminars, 4 hours of practical sessions, 40 hours of independent work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To prepare future primary school teachers for teaching history in forms 5 to 6.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  .
